A vintage 1960s style illustration of an overflowing mailbox on a suburban street, with hundreds of carbon copy papers spilling out and scattering in the wind like autumn leaves. A single figure walks away from the chaos down a clean, empty sidewalk toward a serene horizon, their posture relaxed and unburdened. The color palette features muted teals, warm oranges, and cream tones with subtle halftone dot textures typical of mid-century print advertisements. The mailbox is ornate and brass-colored, overwhelmed and tilting under the paper avalanche, while the path ahead appears crisp and uncluttered.
